post.description:
Migrate all org-stored models to the user's personal HuggingFace account.

@param user_ctx: Authenticated user context.
@returns: List of MigrateModelResponse for each model.

Migrate an org-stored model to the user's personal HuggingFace account.

Uses HF's duplicate_repo for server-side instant copy (no download/upload).
Sequence: make org repo public -> user's token duplicates to personal
namespace -> verify duplicate exists -> delete org repo -> update DB.

Recovers models stuck in 'migrating' status for > 10 minutes (previous
attempt failed and status revert was lost).

@param model_id: The user_models row ID to migrate.
@param user_ctx: Authenticated user context.
@returns: MigrateModelResponse with the new repo ID.
@throws HTTPException 400: Model is not org-stored, or no personal HF token.
@throws HTTPException 404: Model not found.
@throws HTTPException 409: Migration already in progress.
@throws HTTPException 500: Migration failed.

Create a Stripe Checkout Session for a specific price or custom amount.

Accepts either ``price_id`` (existing Stripe price, supports subscriptions)
or ``amount`` (custom amount in cents, one-time payment against the
configured API Credits product).

@param price_id: Stripe Price ID for a pre-defined plan.
@param amount: Custom amount in cents (min 500 / $5.00, max 50000 / $500.00).
@param user: Authenticated user (injected via ``verify_jwt``).
@returns: JSON with a ``url`` field pointing to the Stripe Checkout page.
@throws HTTPException 400: Neither ``price_id`` nor ``amount`` provided,
    or ``amount`` is outside the allowed range.
@throws HTTPException 403: Email address is not verified.
@throws HTTPException 500: Stripe API failure.
